      <td>Update profile and upload photo</td>
      <td>Profile data saved successfully</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <div class="subsection">8.3 Expected Output</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Successful role-based login and redirection.</li>
    <li>Correct user and branch management by admin.</li>
    <li>Valid marks insertion and update by professor.</li>
    <li>Accurate grade computation and dashboard summaries.</li>
    <li>Timely student notifications after mark updates.</li>
    <li>Successful PDF and Excel report generation.</li>
    <li>Secure password reset and profile management workflows.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="section">9. RESULT</div>
  <p>
    The <b>Student Performance Analysis System</b> was successfully designed and implemented as a web-based
    academic management application. The system provides secure role-based access for <b>Admin</b>,
    <b>Professor</b>, and <b>Student</b> users. It supports user management, branch handling, subject
    management, marks entry, analytics, notifications, profile updates, and report generation.
    The project reduces manual effort, improves accuracy in academic record handling, and provides useful
    performance insights for students, faculty, and administration. Hence, the project satisfies the intended
    objectives of a practical student performance monitoring system.
  </p>

  <div class="section">10. ADVANTAGES OF THE SYSTEM</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Reduces manual paperwork and repetitive effort.</li>
    <li>Improves data accuracy and consistency.</li>
    <li>Provides centralized access to academic records.</li>
    <li>Improves transparency for students.</li>
    <li>Supports report generation in PDF and Excel formats.</li>
    <li>Provides analytics useful for academic planning.</li>
    <li>Can be extended with additional institutional modules.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="section">11. LIMITATIONS OF THE SYSTEM</div>
  <ul>
    <li>The system depends on proper and authorized data entry.</li>
    <li>SQLite is best suited for small to medium academic deployments.</li>
    <li>Continuous server and browser access are required in deployed environments.</li>
    <li>Role mapping and branch data must be maintained accurately.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="section">12. FUTURE ENHANCEMENTS</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Attendance-based performance tracking and integrated analytics.</li>
    <li>Internal and external examination separation.</li>
    <li>Graphical performance charts using advanced visualization tools.</li>
    <li>Mobile application support.</li>
    <li>Parent login and guardian notifications.</li>
    <li>AI-based prediction for identifying at-risk students.</li>
    <li>SMS and email academic alert enhancements.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="section">13. CONCLUSION</div>
  <p>
    This project demonstrates the practical application of software engineering concepts, web development,
    database design, and system modeling in a real academic domain. The Student Performance Analysis System
    offers an effective, reliable, and scalable solution for digitizing student academic record management.
    It can serve as a strong foundation for future academic management enhancements in educational institutions.
  </p>
